HEADWORD: Polymeniscous
<hw>Pol`y*me*nis"cous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Poly-</er>, and <er>Meniscus</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Having numerous facets; -- said of the compound eyes of insects and
crustaceans.</def>⟦br⟧
